Advance width of 'thinspace' (uni2009) should be smaller than the advance width of 'space' (uni0020).

Advance width 'thinspace' 595 is greater than 'space' 118, but should be smaller (usually 60% of 'space').

Error

hmtx

Index 2 and 595

Advance width of 'hairspace' (uni200A) should be smaller than the advance width of 'space' (uni0020).

Advance width 'hairspace' 594 is greater than 'space' 118, but should be smaller (usually 30% of 'space').

STAT

static font

Variable font must have a STAT table.

No check of STAT table for static fonts included, yet. Static fonts do not need to have a STAT table. It is only recommended by Microsoft, not required.
More infos here:
https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/typography/opentype/spec/stat

Info

name

Mac NID 0 (1, 0, 0, 0)

Mac NID 0, Copyright.

Please verify agains spec.
Mac NID 0 is 'Copyright 2013 The Alegreya Sans Project Authors (https://github.com/huertatipografica/Alegreya-Sans)'
It should follow this structure: 'Copyright (c) XXXX - XXXX /entity/. All rights reserved.'

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Alegreya Sans SC' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin' = NID 1 'Alegreya Sans SC Thin'.

Alegreya Sans SC Thin Italic (AlegreyaSansSC-ThinItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'AlegreyaSansSC-ThinItalic', Everything looks good.

Alegreya Sans SC Thin Italic (AlegreyaSansSC-ThinItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Alegreya Sans SC' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin Italic' = NID 1 'Alegreya Sans SC Thin' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Alegreya Sans SC Light Italic (AlegreyaSansSC-LightItalic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'AlegreyaSansSC-LightItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Alegreya Sans SC Light Italic (AlegreyaSansSC-LightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'AlegreyaSansSC-LightItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Alegreya Sans SC Light Italic (AlegreyaSansSC-LightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Alegreya Sans SC' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light Italic' = NID 1 'Alegreya Sans SC Light' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

NID 6 is 'AlegreyaSansSC-Italic', Everything looks good.

Alegreya Sans SC Italic (AlegreyaSansSC-Italic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'AlegreyaSansSC-Italic', Everything looks good.

Pass

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Alegreya Sans SC' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium' = NID 1 'Alegreya Sans SC Medium'.

Alegreya Sans SC Medium Italic (AlegreyaSansSC-MediumItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'AlegreyaSansSC-MediumItalic', Everything looks good.

Alegreya Sans SC Medium Italic (AlegreyaSansSC-MediumItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Alegreya Sans SC' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium Italic' = NID 1 'Alegreya Sans SC Medium' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.

NID 6 is 'AlegreyaSansSC-BoldItalic', Everything looks good.

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Alegreya Sans SC' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraBold' = NID 1 'Alegreya Sans SC ExtraBold'.

Alegreya Sans SC Black Regular (AlegreyaSansSC-Black.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Alegreya Sans SC' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Black' = NID 1 'Alegreya Sans SC Black'.

MS NID 16/17

NID 16 'Alegreya Sans SC' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Black Italic' = NID 1 'Alegreya Sans SC Black' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.
